recsuccesstitle:
The title of a page containing a success message.

Parameters:
* $1 - will contain the category of pages to be created, e.g. Event
recsuccess:
A success message. Parameters:
* $1 - number of pages
recsuccess-returntoorigin:
Provides navigation back to the origin page. Parameters:
* $1 - the origin page title, with link
recerror: The title of en error page
recerror-noiteratorname: An error message. See the [[wikipedia:Iterator | wikipedia page]] for the meaning of iterator. The name of the parameter in quotes should not be translated!
recerror-iteratorunknown: {{doc-important|The name of the parameter "iterator" in quotes should not be translated!}} Used as fatal error message. See the [[wikipedia:Iterator | wikipedia page]] for the meaning of iterator. Parameters: * $1 - iterator name
recerror-noformname: An error message. The name of the parameter in quotes should not be translated!
recerror-formunknown:
Used as fatal error message. Parameters:
* $1 - form name
recerror-notargetformname: An error message. The name of the parameter in quotes should not be translated!
recerror-notargetfieldname: An error message. The name of the parameter in quotes should not be translated!
recerror-iteratorparammissing: {{doc-important|Do not translate "#reclink".}} An error message. See the [[wikipedia:Iterator | wikipedia page]] for the meaning of iterator. Parameters: * $1 - list of error messages (unordered list)
recerror-noiteratordata: An error message. See the [[wikipedia:Iterator | wikipedia page]] for the meaning of iterator.
recerror-pagegenerationlimitexeeded:
Used as error message. Parameters:
* $1 - number of pages (number of iterator values)
* $2 - limit number of pages
recerror-date-internalerror:
An error message. "the dates" doesn't contain times. Parameters:
* $1 - "Unknown error. This could be due to a malformed start or end date." (in English), or a list of errors
